---
description: Documentation standards and best practices for maintaining clear and comprehensive project documentation.
alwaysApply: false
---

- All new features must be documented in the project's README or a dedicated docs folder.
- All breaking changes must be documented in a CHANGELOG.
- All utility functions and hooks must have usage examples in the documentation.
- Maintain an up-to-date architecture diagram in the docs.
- All environment variables must be documented in an .env.example file.
